# PROJECT: rhai-runtime

## Goal
A standalone CLI binary that turns Rhai into a general-purpose scripting runtime — the missing `rhai script.rhai` equivalent of `python script.py`. Rust is the engine; the binary exposes filesystem, shell, environment, and HTTP APIs to Rhai scripts. No new syntax is invented — Rhai is the language, Rust is the host.

## Stack
- Language: Rust 2021, stable toolchain
- Scripting: rhai = { version = "1", features = ["serde"] }
- HTTP: ureq = { version = "2", features = ["json"] }
- Serialisation: serde_json = "1"
- Error handling: thiserror (core), anyhow (CLI boundary only)
- Logging: tracing + tracing-subscriber

## Structure
- src:      src/
- std:      std/          (importable Rhai standard library modules)
- examples: examples/
- proj:     proj/
- config:   N/A (no runtime config file yet)

## Method
- Workflow: PROJECT → FIXES → TODO → code → test → DONE
- Branching: feature branches, never commit to main
- Testing: cargo test (unit) + integration tests via examples/
- Build: cargo build --release

## Patterns
- api-registration: All Rhai API functions are registered in src/api/ modules, wired in main.rs
- state-per-concern: Compile-time constants live in src/state/ (sizes, durations, limits, paths)
- error-newtype: Each API module defines its own error enum with thiserror; anyhow wraps at CLI entry

